args:
When Elysium descends, he is wholly unlike the
Holywyrm from the history that Zethia knows.
After he holds the people of the capital hostage
and demands Ilia form a pact, she reluctantly
accedes. However, a pactstone called Dragalia
then pierces her chest, causing her to collapse.
So this is where you were, Windwyrm.
Then you know what the world\nlooks like at present.
If such is true, you must be prepared\nto accept my true feelings now.
No. For no matter the state of this world,\nI cannot approve of your methods.
With dragons controlling the activity of\nall mana, humanity will be little more\nthan our servants—or slaves.
You seek to force the subservience of\nhumanity—nay, of all life!
No! The Holywyrm would never do such!
This is what I was trying to explain earlier:\nThe Elysium from OUR world is veeery\ndifferent from the one you seem to know.
Hear me well, human whelps: As a\nspecies, you are yet young and immature.
You wield power frivolously, without a care\nin your heads as to how your actions\nmight affect the greater world at large.
You are pathetic creatures who devour\nyourselves in a desperate scrabble to\nsurvive just one more day.
If left to your own devices, you shall walk\ninexorably down the path to ruin and bring\nthe rest of the world down with you.
I can no longer overlook this.\nThis is salvation. It is relief.
Even if this WERE salvation, accepting it\nmeans we never grow and change—we'll\nremain ＂whelps＂ forever!
If that's relief, I'll take my chances, thanks.
I wonder if you will be able to say the\nsame as you gaze upon this tragedy.
Blinded by their own greed,\nthey do not balk at harming others.
THIS is the current state of humans.
They drill into and wound the very earth\nupon which they rely.

If you humans possessed the ability or
desire to stop this rampage, you would
have done so long ago. The fact you have
not serves as proof you CANNOT.
Consequently, a third party must save you;\nyou require the management of a more\nmature life form.
Look, if you want to say humanity is\nimmature and bone-headed, you won't\nget any kind of argument from me.
But that doesn't give dragons an excuse\nto force us into servitude.
I seek not servitude, but control.
Pretty words. Whatever savior you might\nthink yourself, you reject human will and\nattempt to subjugate it to that of dragons.
If not servitude, what would you name it?

Can you not wait yet a while, Holywyrm?
As you say, humanity is immature—which
makes all the more reason we ought to
watch over them as they learn and grow.
He's right, you know? We CAN learn—\nand as we do, we'll pave the way to a\nnew kinship between our species!
I fear the hour is far too late for grace\nconsidering the continued barbarism\nand rampage of you human whelps.
Your salvation begins here and now.
Salvation? It's more like slavery!\nSo who's rampaging on who here?!
If you want to make people submit to you,\nyou shouldn't care about me—you should\nset your sights on the kingdom.
I'm just an alchemist—a random woman.\nWhat value can I possibly have?
Our fates were linked, long, long ago.\nYou are the beating heart of your people,\nstretching back to the very first of them.
Neither your understanding nor willingness\nis necessary as regards this truth.
As a child, I worshipped you like a god.\nI believed you would guide me.
But I was wrong. You were just observing.
My young body couldn't withstand a pact of\nservitude, so you were just hanging around\nuntil I grew up a little more.
When I learned your true intentions,\nit broke my heart. But it's different now.
Now the idea of worshipping you\njust makes me laugh.
I'd sooner become a god myself\nthan help make YOU one.
And that is what you will become if you\nforge this pact: A god in human form.
People will listen to you. Obey your will.\nWORSHIP you.

And that whole time, they'd actually be
praying to YOU—the god behind the
curtain. I'd be no better than a puppet.
It's a horrifying thought.
So no thanks, Elysium. I'll find another\nway to put an end to this war.
Your decision will lead to a great many\nsacrifices, dragon and human alike.
This very moment, destruction looms for\nthe city you name the royal capital, in the\nform of mana twisted by human hands.
So the dragons are still approaching\nthe city while we've been standing here?
You human whelps do not comprehend\nthat if so much mana is set ablaze,\nit is not only your city that will burn.
Once alight, the burning mana will spread\nout and engulf the world in an eyeblink.
All the more reason we have to stop it!
Unfortunately, the spark is ready to light.
Your wingless bodies will not\nmake it in time.
The destruction of the world begins this\nday because of humans. However...
I could save the world—or YOU could!
You're talking about making a pact.
Forge a pact and entrust to me the\nworkings of mana. If you do this,\nI will be able to stem the flow.
With this single choice, you alone\ndetermine the fate of this world.
I have no need to lie.
There's just no other way, Meene.\n...Elysium. Promise me you'll protect\neverything in this world.
Of course. That is why I am here.
Repeat after me, Ilia:\n＂I pledge, in the name of the first...＂
I pledge, in the name of the first...
Rest in peace, Ilia, and know the\nsalvation of the world begins now.
WHAT DID YOU DO?!\nWHAT DID YOU DO TO ILIA?!
A pactstone has been created from my\nself—a pactstone called Dragalia.

By piercing through the Primal Mark with 
said pactstone, a true pact is formed and
the workings of mana come under my
control.
M-Mordecai, no! You must calm yourself!\nSuch rage could lead to—
It is the Other... It is Morsayati!
(At that moment, I finally realized\nwhat a terrible mistake I had made.)
(If the history I believed in was sham...)
(If the tragedy unfolding before me\nwas the truth of history...)
